{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, we emphasize that preservation strategies are required to ensure that reviews remain accessible in the future.",
    "We also encourage preprint servers to import or aggregate links to external preprint reviews, as is currently done by bioRxiv.",
    "In the absence of such integrations, readers may be inclined to post reviews via the commenting system of the preprint server.",
    "Such systems do not currently issue DOIs or any other form of persistent identifier.",
    "Ideally commenters posting reviews should also provide an authenticated ORCID, but this may create a barrier to entry, so tension between best practices for long-term discoverability and adoption exists."
  ]
}